WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.462 align:middle line:90%


00:00:16.462 --> 00:00:17.170 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA GARR: Hi.

00:00:17.170 --> 00:00:18.919 align:middle line:84%
I'm Lisa Garr, host
of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:18.919 --> 00:00:21.140 align:middle line:84%
We are broadcasting from
the Conscious Life Expo

00:00:21.140 --> 00:00:23.550 align:middle line:84%
here in Los Angeles,
and joining me again

00:00:23.550 --> 00:00:24.520 align:middle line:90%
is Marianne Williamson.

00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:26.600 align:middle line:84%
She is running for
Congress for the US

00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:29.520 align:middle line:84%
House of Representatives,
and she is here again

00:00:29.520 --> 00:00:31.450 align:middle line:84%
to talk about the
new conversation

00:00:31.450 --> 00:00:33.060 align:middle line:84%
that people are
having, that Americans

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:35.111 align:middle line:84%
particularly, are
having about politics.

00:00:35.111 --> 00:00:36.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm so glad you're back.

00:00:36.110 --> 00:00:37.030 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:00:37.030 --> 00:00:38.320 align:middle line:84%
>> MARIANNE WILLIAMSON: Thank
you so much for having me.

00:00:38.320 --> 00:00:38.580 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yeah.

00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:40.871 align:middle line:84%
I'm glad we caught you here
in the middle of everything

00:00:40.871 --> 00:00:42.740 align:middle line:84%
that you're doing and
your entire campaign.

00:00:42.740 --> 00:00:44.739 align:middle line:84%
So a few things have
changed since the last time

00:00:44.739 --> 00:00:47.330 align:middle line:84%
that we've spoken
here on Gaiam TV.

00:00:47.330 --> 00:00:49.640 align:middle line:84%
Henry Waxman is
no longer running.

00:00:49.640 --> 00:00:52.582 align:middle line:84%
How did that impact your
campaign, or did it?

00:00:52.582 --> 00:00:54.290 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Well,
it certainly changes

00:00:54.290 --> 00:00:55.790 align:middle line:90%
the landscape.

00:00:55.790 --> 00:00:57.030 align:middle line:90%
The molecules are different.

00:00:57.030 --> 00:00:59.909 align:middle line:10%
Congressman Waxman has
been there for 38 years.

00:00:59.909 --> 00:01:00.450 align:middle line:10%
>> LISA: Wow.

00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:03.820 align:middle line:10%
>> WILLIAMSON: And so I was
running against an incumbent.

00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:09.150 align:middle line:10%
And now whoever is elected will
be a first-term congressperson.

00:01:09.150 --> 00:01:10.340 align:middle line:10%
So it's different.

00:01:10.340 --> 00:01:14.940 align:middle line:10%
There are two new
candidates since he

00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:16.372 align:middle line:10%
announced his retirement.

00:01:16.372 --> 00:01:18.080 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: And there
will be probably more.

00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:19.330 align:middle line:90%
>> WILLIAMSON: There might be.

00:01:19.330 --> 00:01:20.460 align:middle line:90%
There absolutely might be.

00:01:20.460 --> 00:01:22.236 align:middle line:90%
So it's different.

00:01:22.236 --> 00:01:23.360 align:middle line:90%
There's no better or worse.

00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:24.735 align:middle line:84%
It's just a little
bit different.

00:01:24.735 --> 00:01:29.920 align:middle line:84%
But my message was not tailored
to Congressman Waxman's being

00:01:29.920 --> 00:01:32.830 align:middle line:84%
in office, and it's not tailored
to his not being in office.

00:01:32.830 --> 00:01:35.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm speaking about something
that's the same message before

00:01:35.510 --> 00:01:36.540 align:middle line:90%
and the message now.

00:01:36.540 --> 00:01:37.740 align:middle line:90%
That's not going to change.

00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:39.090 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Which is?

00:01:39.090 --> 00:01:43.820 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: I feel that there
has been a very undemocratic

00:01:43.820 --> 00:01:47.040 align:middle line:84%
trend in the United States
over the last few years.

00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:48.860 align:middle line:84%
We've got shrinking
civil liberties, things

00:01:48.860 --> 00:01:50.693 align:middle line:84%
that every American
should be very concerned

00:01:50.693 --> 00:01:53.981 align:middle line:84%
about, whether it's the domestic
spying or the National Defense

00:01:53.981 --> 00:01:56.480 align:middle line:84%
Authorization Act that allows
the government to indefinitely

00:01:56.480 --> 00:01:58.980 align:middle line:84%
detain US citizens-- I don't
think most Americans are really

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:02.100 align:middle line:84%
focusing on what that means--
drones that will be here

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:02.924 align:middle line:90%
in two years.

00:02:02.924 --> 00:02:03.590 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Drones?

00:02:03.590 --> 00:02:05.215 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: So
there's a shrinking--

00:02:05.215 --> 00:02:07.650 align:middle line:84%
drones are the
unmanned aircraft.

00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:12.100 align:middle line:84%
Which, you know, drones,
when you think of the drones

00:02:12.100 --> 00:02:13.570 align:middle line:84%
as they're used in
other countries,

00:02:13.570 --> 00:02:15.250 align:middle line:90%
they have this radar, right?

00:02:15.250 --> 00:02:18.230 align:middle line:84%
So when the drones
get here, they

00:02:18.230 --> 00:02:20.500 align:middle line:84%
could know, Lisa, who
you're sleeping with

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:22.460 align:middle line:84%
and what room you
just walked into

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:24.810 align:middle line:84%
and what you're logging
onto on your computer.

00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:26.280 align:middle line:84%
Now we're being
told that they're

00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:29.165 align:middle line:84%
going to be used by
amazon.com and FedEx

00:02:29.165 --> 00:02:32.120 align:middle line:84%
and by law enforcement
to catch the bad guys

00:02:32.120 --> 00:02:35.200 align:middle line:84%
and that we shouldn't worry
about privacy because they will

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:40.060 align:middle line:84%
have to adhere to all state and
local and federal privacy laws.

00:02:40.060 --> 00:02:40.620 align:middle line:90%
But in--

00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:41.870 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Whatever those are.

00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:45.460 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: --the days of NSA
spying when we're already told

00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:47.100 align:middle line:84%
we're spying on
your phone calls,

00:02:47.100 --> 00:02:49.050 align:middle line:84%
a lot of Americans on
the left and the right--

00:02:49.050 --> 00:02:50.850 align:middle line:84%
this has nothing to do
with left or right--

00:02:50.850 --> 00:02:53.090 align:middle line:84%
a lot of Americans are
saying, what is going on here?

00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:54.881 align:middle line:84%
So we have these
shrinking civil liberties,

00:02:54.881 --> 00:02:57.820 align:middle line:84%
we have expanding
corporate influence,

00:02:57.820 --> 00:02:59.530 align:middle line:84%
and we have domestic
surveillance.

00:02:59.530 --> 00:03:02.690 align:middle line:90%
So these form a very toxic brew.

00:03:02.690 --> 00:03:03.790 align:middle line:90%
It's a real poison.

00:03:03.790 --> 00:03:05.590 align:middle line:84%
You can either have
a democracy or not.

00:03:05.590 --> 00:03:08.590 align:middle line:84%
And if you have a democracy
and you care about that,

00:03:08.590 --> 00:03:10.750 align:middle line:84%
then you want to really
think very strongly

00:03:10.750 --> 00:03:13.040 align:middle line:84%
about the kind of changes
that are being made here.

00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:16.120 align:middle line:84%
We're currently basically making
a mockery of the Gettysburg

00:03:16.120 --> 00:03:17.030 align:middle line:90%
Address.

00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:18.580 align:middle line:84%
Because when
Lincoln said we were

00:03:18.580 --> 00:03:21.730 align:middle line:84%
a government of the people, by
the people, and for the people

00:03:21.730 --> 00:03:24.360 align:middle line:84%
and that those men had
died in that battle

00:03:24.360 --> 00:03:26.510 align:middle line:84%
so that a government of
the people, by the people,

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:29.450 align:middle line:84%
and for the people would
not perish from the earth,

00:03:29.450 --> 00:03:31.160 align:middle line:84%
I believe it's
perishing, because we've

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:33.280 align:middle line:84%
become a government
of a few of the people

00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:36.130 align:middle line:84%
and by a few of the people
and for a few the people.

00:03:36.130 --> 00:03:39.730 align:middle line:84%
And those moneyed interests
represented by that,

00:03:39.730 --> 00:03:42.920 align:middle line:84%
moneyed interests influence
our political functioning

00:03:42.920 --> 00:03:45.560 align:middle line:84%
in a way that is
so disproportionate

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:48.870 align:middle line:84%
to the influence that is
wielded by the average citizen

00:03:48.870 --> 00:03:51.380 align:middle line:84%
as to form of real
crisis of our democracy.

00:03:51.380 --> 00:03:54.020 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: So if you get into
this office and you see these

00:03:54.020 --> 00:03:57.280 align:middle line:84%
moneyed corporate interests in
your environment and that you

00:03:57.280 --> 00:04:00.060 align:middle line:84%
have a direct ability to
make an impact on this,

00:04:00.060 --> 00:04:00.980 align:middle line:90%
what will you do?

00:04:00.980 --> 00:04:02.110 align:middle line:90%
How will you start?

00:04:02.110 --> 00:04:04.790 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Well, I would
be one of 435 congresspeople,

00:04:04.790 --> 00:04:06.850 align:middle line:84%
and there are, in the
Senate and in the House,

00:04:06.850 --> 00:04:11.350 align:middle line:84%
people already working towards
a constitutional amendment that

00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:14.270 align:middle line:84%
would outlaw the undo influence
of money on our politics

00:04:14.270 --> 00:04:17.300 align:middle line:84%
and declare that corporations do
not have the right personhood.

00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:19.985 align:middle line:84%
Just the other day there was
a bill introduced in the House

00:04:19.985 --> 00:04:21.360 align:middle line:84%
that has to do
with an issue that

00:04:21.360 --> 00:04:23.193 align:middle line:84%
would have to do with
making certain amounts

00:04:23.193 --> 00:04:26.810 align:middle line:84%
of political contributions tax
deductible, which they aren't

00:04:26.810 --> 00:04:28.910 align:middle line:84%
now, matching funds
from the government.

00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:31.640 align:middle line:84%
So this is a conversation
that's already happening.

00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:33.670 align:middle line:84%
Many Americans are
looking around and going,

00:04:33.670 --> 00:04:35.970 align:middle line:84%
who does this country
belong to anymore?

00:04:35.970 --> 00:04:36.565 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yes.

00:04:36.565 --> 00:04:37.940 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON:
From a perspective

00:04:37.940 --> 00:04:42.360 align:middle line:84%
of transformational, we
understand about subconscious

00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:45.220 align:middle line:84%
forces, and we have
subconsciously recreated

00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:47.010 align:middle line:90%
an aristocracy.

00:04:47.010 --> 00:04:50.020 align:middle line:84%
And this country was founded
to repudiate an aristocracy,

00:04:50.020 --> 00:04:51.944 align:middle line:84%
and we need to
repudiate it again.

00:04:51.944 --> 00:04:53.360 align:middle line:84%
Because this country
should belong

00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:54.780 align:middle line:84%
to the people of
the United States.

00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:56.738 align:middle line:84%
The people of the United
States should not just

00:04:56.738 --> 00:04:59.750 align:middle line:84%
be receiving the crumbs
that are left over

00:04:59.750 --> 00:05:02.280 align:middle line:84%
after multinational corporate
interests have basically

00:05:02.280 --> 00:05:03.660 align:middle line:90%
taken whatever they want.

00:05:03.660 --> 00:05:05.410 align:middle line:84%
That's not what America
is supposed to be.

00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:07.740 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: It's also a loss
of our civil liberties

00:05:07.740 --> 00:05:09.040 align:middle line:90%
to the corporations.

00:05:09.040 --> 00:05:11.600 align:middle line:84%
So let me ask you about
where you came from.

00:05:11.600 --> 00:05:13.864 align:middle line:84%
You started off as a teacher
of A Course in Miracles,

00:05:13.864 --> 00:05:16.280 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: I still am a
teacher of Course in Miracles.

00:05:16.280 --> 00:05:16.821 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yes.

00:05:16.821 --> 00:05:20.170 align:middle line:84%
And so how are you
infusing that conversation?

00:05:20.170 --> 00:05:22.890 align:middle line:84%
Your roots from what you
wrote, A Return to Love,

00:05:22.890 --> 00:05:26.447 align:middle line:84%
and your best-selling book
on-- how are you infusing that

00:05:26.447 --> 00:05:27.780 align:middle line:90%
into the political conversation?

00:05:27.780 --> 00:05:29.840 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Well, I believe
there's one truth spoken

00:05:29.840 --> 00:05:32.020 align:middle line:84%
in many different ways, whether
it's A Course in Miracles

00:05:32.020 --> 00:05:34.561 align:middle line:84%
or any other serious spiritual
path, path of personal growth,

00:05:34.561 --> 00:05:36.940 align:middle line:84%
recovery, spirituality,
and all that.

00:05:36.940 --> 00:05:39.110 align:middle line:84%
And one of the issues
is that a person

00:05:39.110 --> 00:05:41.900 align:middle line:84%
is as sick as their
secrets, as they say in AA.

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:43.600 align:middle line:90%
Well, so is a nation.

00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:45.750 align:middle line:84%
And because for
the last 30 years

00:05:45.750 --> 00:05:48.029 align:middle line:84%
I've been up close and
personal with people in crisis,

00:05:48.029 --> 00:05:49.570 align:middle line:84%
basically-- I always
say people don't

00:05:49.570 --> 00:05:50.860 align:middle line:84%
come to me because
things are going well.

00:05:50.860 --> 00:05:51.443 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yeah.

00:05:51.443 --> 00:05:53.260 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: So we
know about crisis,

00:05:53.260 --> 00:05:56.200 align:middle line:84%
and we know that in order to
transition out of a crisis,

00:05:56.200 --> 00:06:00.650 align:middle line:84%
you have to have a deep inquiry
into who you are and what

00:06:00.650 --> 00:06:03.700 align:middle line:84%
you're doing and whether you are
aligned with the principles you

00:06:03.700 --> 00:06:06.540 align:middle line:84%
believe in and where you need
to change and where you need

00:06:06.540 --> 00:06:10.340 align:middle line:84%
to atone and where you need to
make amends and where you need

00:06:10.340 --> 00:06:11.490 align:middle line:90%
to course-correct.

00:06:11.490 --> 00:06:15.030 align:middle line:84%
And I think America, those same
principles of consciousness

00:06:15.030 --> 00:06:17.770 align:middle line:84%
that rule an individual's
life rule a national life,

00:06:17.770 --> 00:06:20.150 align:middle line:84%
because all that a nation is
is a group of individuals.

00:06:20.150 --> 00:06:24.620 align:middle line:84%
America has to now enter into
a deep inquiry into who we are.

00:06:24.620 --> 00:06:26.780 align:middle line:84%
And that's why politics,
as Gandhi said,

00:06:26.780 --> 00:06:27.972 align:middle line:90%
politics should be sacred.

00:06:27.972 --> 00:06:30.180 align:middle line:84%
It should be the place where
we're having the deepest

00:06:30.180 --> 00:06:32.690 align:middle line:84%
conversation, and it
is instead a place

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:35.030 align:middle line:84%
where we have the most
shallow conversation.

00:06:35.030 --> 00:06:37.410 align:middle line:84%
Now you and I know, two
people, let's get down,

00:06:37.410 --> 00:06:39.050 align:middle line:84%
let's have a real
conversation, Lisa.

00:06:39.050 --> 00:06:39.380 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yeah.

00:06:39.380 --> 00:06:41.210 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Let's really
get down and have an authentic

00:06:41.210 --> 00:06:42.557 align:middle line:90%
conversation on what's true.

00:06:42.557 --> 00:06:44.390 align:middle line:84%
We know what that does
for our relationship.

00:06:44.390 --> 00:06:44.740 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yes.

00:06:44.740 --> 00:06:45.780 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: We know
what that does for you.

00:06:45.780 --> 00:06:46.650 align:middle line:90%
We know what it does for me.

00:06:46.650 --> 00:06:47.130 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Yes.

00:06:47.130 --> 00:06:48.130 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON:
Politics should be--

00:06:48.130 --> 00:06:48.950 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: It makes us deeper--

00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:49.370 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON:
--where have that--

00:06:49.370 --> 00:06:49.925 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: It makes
us more connected.

00:06:49.925 --> 00:06:52.310 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: --same
authentic powerful conversation

00:06:52.310 --> 00:06:54.374 align:middle line:90%
collectively.

00:06:54.374 --> 00:06:57.040 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: It doesn't even feel to
me like that would be possible.

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:58.010 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Well,
it is possible.

00:06:58.010 --> 00:06:58.780 align:middle line:90%
We're doing it right now.

00:06:58.780 --> 00:06:59.840 align:middle line:90%
We're doing it here.

00:06:59.840 --> 00:07:05.004 align:middle line:84%
In every campaign event that
I am part of, I'm so grateful.

00:07:05.004 --> 00:07:07.420 align:middle line:84%
I feel there's a real listening
from people who want that.

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:08.380 align:middle line:90%
We yearn for that.

00:07:08.380 --> 00:07:09.850 align:middle line:84%
And, you know, I
tell you, people

00:07:09.850 --> 00:07:11.510 align:middle line:90%
want it in Washington, too.

00:07:11.510 --> 00:07:14.424 align:middle line:84%
It's just that the system
that has been forged--

00:07:14.424 --> 00:07:16.090 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: It's not set
up for that, yeah.

00:07:16.090 --> 00:07:18.256 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Well, I don't
know if it's not set up

00:07:18.256 --> 00:07:20.570 align:middle line:84%
for that, but it has become
because of the dominance

00:07:20.570 --> 00:07:23.820 align:middle line:84%
of money that politicians
feel they need in order to get

00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.100 align:middle line:90%
elected and to stay elected.

00:07:25.100 --> 00:07:27.090 align:middle line:90%
But we can change that.

00:07:27.090 --> 00:07:29.396 align:middle line:84%
You change things one
conversation at a time.

00:07:29.396 --> 00:07:32.020 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: What conversations are
you having with the people that

00:07:32.020 --> 00:07:34.570 align:middle line:84%
are supporting you or even
that you're hearing from

00:07:34.570 --> 00:07:35.440 align:middle line:90%
in Washington?

00:07:35.440 --> 00:07:37.680 align:middle line:84%
Are they having
this conversation?

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:40.320 align:middle line:84%
>> WILLIAMSON: Many people in
America are aware that we are

00:07:40.320 --> 00:07:40.910 align:middle line:90%
in crisis.

00:07:40.910 --> 00:07:42.727 align:middle line:84%
Many people are
aware that huge oil

00:07:42.727 --> 00:07:44.310 align:middle line:84%
companies and
pharmaceutical companies

00:07:44.310 --> 00:07:48.040 align:middle line:84%
and health insurance companies
and big agricultural companies

00:07:48.040 --> 00:07:50.830 align:middle line:84%
and prison industrial
complex companies

00:07:50.830 --> 00:07:52.372 align:middle line:84%
and military
contractors-- people-- I

00:07:52.372 --> 00:07:54.413 align:middle line:84%
don't care if you're on
the right or on the left.

00:07:54.413 --> 00:07:57.130 align:middle line:84%
This is not a right/left issue
at the deepest-- are like,

00:07:57.130 --> 00:07:58.600 align:middle line:90%
what's going on?

00:07:58.600 --> 00:08:01.180 align:middle line:84%
And I think people
appreciate-- and that's,

00:08:01.180 --> 00:08:04.095 align:middle line:84%
of course, the reason I'm
running as an independent is

00:08:04.095 --> 00:08:07.170 align:middle line:84%
because I think that if
you're unshackled by the dogma

00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:10.660 align:middle line:84%
or doctrine or rules of any
particular political party,

00:08:10.660 --> 00:08:13.150 align:middle line:84%
and if you're running a
grassroots campaign, as I am,

